<quantity box="[614,717,1442,1468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="597" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.70 mm</quantity>
. Antenna with 28 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,928,1442,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">–</emphasis>
30 flagellomeres. Head mostly yellow except for melanic scape, flagellomeres and occiput at the ocellar triangle. Mandibles white with melanic teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1423,1478,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,790,814]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,764]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,179,764]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Therophilus shimborii sp. n. 1, habitus lateral; 2, head, front view; 3, hind wing detail; 4, dorsal view of head and mesosoma; 5, metasoma, 6, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142149/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Interantennal space with one keel-like carina declining posteriorly. Propleuron yellow. Mesoscutum yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1422,1514,1540]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,790,814]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,764]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,179,764]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Therophilus shimborii sp. n. 1, habitus lateral; 2, head, front view; 3, hind wing detail; 4, dorsal view of head and mesosoma; 5, metasoma, 6, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142149/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), notauli meeting and crenulate on posterior third. Propodeum usually yellow, rarely melanic. Sclerite between coxa and metasomal foramen complete and narrow. Hind legs yellow except for distal tip of tibia and tarsi (melanic). Metasoma mostly yellow posterior three terga brownish (
<figureCitation box="[810,881,1622,1649]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,790,814]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,764]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,179,764]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Therophilus shimborii sp. n. 1, habitus lateral; 2, head, front view; 3, hind wing detail; 4, dorsal view of head and mesosoma; 5, metasoma, 6, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142149/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). First metasomal tergum smooth with two well defined carinae extending to 2/3 of tergum length and diverging medially (
<figureCitation box="[984,1052,1658,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,790,814]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,764]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,179,764]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Therophilus shimborii sp. n. 1, habitus lateral; 2, head, front view; 3, hind wing detail; 4, dorsal view of head and mesosoma; 5, metasoma, 6, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142149/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Wings (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1227,1658,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,790,814]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,181,764]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,179,764]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Therophilus shimborii sp. n. 1, habitus lateral; 2, head, front view; 3, hind wing detail; 4, dorsal view of head and mesosoma; 5, metasoma, 6, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142149/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="597">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) evenly hyaline or pale. Fore wing cubital cell triangular and sessile, RS+M vein incomplete and tubular in less than ¼ its length.
</paragraph>
